EMPLOYEE MANAGEMENT LIGHTNING WEB COMPONENT - COMPLETE STEPS FROM CREATION TO RUNNING

1. Open Salesforce Developer Edition.

2. Click Gear icon on top-right.

3. Click Setup.

4. Open Object Manager.

5. Click Create.

6. Click Custom Object.

7. Create Employee object:

   Label: Employee
   Plural Label: Employees
   Object Name: Employee
   Record Name: Employee Name
   Data Type: Text

8. Tick these options if visible:

   Allow Reports
   Allow Search
   Launch New Custom Tab Wizard after saving this custom object

9. Click Save.

10. If Custom Tab Wizard opens:

   Tab Style: Select any style
   Click Next
   Click Next
   Click Save

11. If tab wizard does not open:

   Go to Setup
   Search Tabs
   Open Tabs
   Under Custom Object Tabs, click New
   Object: Employee
   Tab Style: Select any style
   Click Next
   Click Next
   Click Save

12. Now create fields for Employee object.

13. Go to Setup.

14. Open Object Manager.

15. Open Employee object.

16. Click Fields & Relationships.

17. Click New.

18. Create Employee ID field:

   Data Type: Number
   Field Label: Employee ID
   Length: 10
   Decimal Places: 0
   Field Name: Employee_ID

   Tick Unique if available.

   Click Next
   Click Next
   Click Save & New

19. Create Salary field:

   Data Type: Currency
   Field Label: Salary
   Length: 10
   Decimal Places: 2
   Field Name: Salary

   Click Next
   Click Next
   Click Save & New

20. Create Email field:

   Data Type: Email
   Field Label: Email
   Field Name: Email

   Click Next
   Click Next
   Click Save & New

21. Create Department field:

   Data Type: Picklist
   Field Label: Department
   Field Name: Department

   Enter values, each on a new line:

   HR
   IT
   Finance
   Sales
   Marketing

   Click Next
   Click Next
   Click Save & New

22. Create Joining Date field:

   Data Type: Date
   Field Label: Joining Date
   Field Name: Joining_Date

   Click Next
   Click Next
   Click Save

23. Now create validation rules for Employee object.

24. In Object Manager, open Employee object.

25. Click Validation Rules.

26. Click New.

27. Create validation rule for Employee Name:

   Rule Name:
   Employee_Name_Validation

   Error Condition Formula:

   LEN(Name) < 3

   Error Message:
   Employee Name cannot be empty and must contain at least 3 characters.

   Error Location:
   Top of Page

   Click Save

28. Click New again.

29. Create validation rule for Employee ID:

   Rule Name:
   Employee_ID_Positive_Validation

   Error Condition Formula:

   Employee_ID__c <= 0

   Error Message:
   Employee ID must be greater than 0.

   Error Location:
   Field

   Field:
   Employee ID

   Click Save

30. For Employee ID uniqueness:

   Go to Object Manager
   Open Employee
   Click Fields & Relationships
   Open Employee ID field
   Click Edit
   Tick Unique
   Click Save

31. Click New again under Validation Rules.

32. Create validation rule for Salary:

   Rule Name:
   Employee_Salary_Validation

   Error Condition Formula:

   OR(Salary__c <= 10000, Salary__c >= 500000)

   Error Message:
   Salary must be greater than 10,000 and less than 500,000.

   Error Location:
   Field

   Field:
   Salary

   Click Save

33. Email validation is handled automatically because Email field type is used.

34. Department validation is handled using Picklist field.

35. Click New again.

36. Create validation rule for Joining Date:

   Rule Name:
   Employee_JoiningDate_Validation

   Error Condition Formula:

   Joining_Date__c > TODAY()

   Error Message:
   Joining Date cannot be a future date.

   Error Location:
   Field

   Field:
   Joining Date

   Click Save

