103. Final explanation:

   This Employee Management Lightning Web Component allows users to add employee records.
   Employee object stores all employee data.
   LWC form accepts Employee Name, Employee ID, Salary, Email, Department, and Joining Date.
   JavaScript validation checks the data before saving.
   Validation rules are also created on the object to ensure data accuracy.
   Employee Name must contain at least 3 characters.
   Employee ID must be greater than 0 and unique.
   Salary must be greater than 10,000 and less than 500,000.
   Email must be in valid email format.
   Department must be selected from the picklist.
   Joining Date cannot be a future date.
   If all values are valid, the record is saved using createRecord.
   If any value is invalid, an error message is shown and the record is not saved.
